message: /* Immigration */ Edited section on House immigration reform working group to note that Messer was not a member of the working group; his comments in the MSNBC article are about the working group's plan. See New York Times and Roll Call sources.

Undid revision 792141484 by [[Special:Contributions/Snooganssnoogans|Snooganssnoogans]] ([[User talk:Snooganssnoogans|talk]]) The NBC article does not say Messer was part of the working group. He was commenting on the working group's plan.
/* Residency controversy */ Added details about his family and the rationale for moving his family, as reported by multiple news outlets; Removed the unsourced characterization of McLean as "wealthy"

/* Immigration */ Messer did not lead and was not on the House immigration working group. Membership is listed here http://www.nytimes.com/2013/02/03/us/politics/a-secret-bipartisan-group-with-its-own-immigration-plan.html
/* Private Sector Work */ The last sentence is not factually accurate.
This is a newsworthy, undisputed fact with sources
Rescuing 4 sources and tagging 1 as dead. #IABot (v2.0beta10)
/* top */ Serial commas are awesome. And this needs to remain.
